So basically how the openWRT architecture will work,
The router has a captive portal that sends the user to my app
The app is ran locally on any device prefferably on a raspbery pi
I imagine this product to be a bundle meaning a ready to use out of the box experience:
a router flashed with openwrt and a raspbery pi with the containerized app

-- 
the system is in a vacum meaning it has no need to have internet acces or be connected 
to other systems , everything happens locally and the data is stored inside the rasperypi or 
another machine if atached
basically the captive portal acts as a verifier of the location
the specific instance of the app cannot be accesed outside the router's radius 
